    <main>
      <p>At TalentScaleHQ, we believe in absolute cost transparency for cross-border hiring. Our employment cost calculators are designed to eliminate the "hidden fees" often associated with global teams. Here is how we source and verify our data.</p>

      <h2>1. Base Salary Benchmarks</h2>
      <p>We do not rely on generic crowdsourced data (like standard Glassdoor averages), which often skew low due to domestic, non-English speaking roles. Our base salary figures specifically target <strong>export-grade tech talent</strong> (fluent English, modern tech stacks, US-timezone overlap). Data points are aggregated from:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Verified placements from top LatAm Dev Shops.</li>
        <li>Specialized remote hiring platforms (e.g., Arc.dev, Turing).</li>
        <li>Annual tech compensation reports spanning Q4 2025 to Q1 2026.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Employer Taxes & Statutory Benefits</h2>
      <p>Local labor laws dictate mandatory employer burdens (Employer Payroll Taxes). We manually verify these percentages against official government tax directives and cross-reference them with Tier-1 Employer of Record (EOR) public guidelines (such as Deel and Remote).</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Mandatory Bonuses:</strong> Factored into the total cost (e.g., the 13th-month <em>Prima</em> in Colombia, or <em>Aguinaldo</em> in Mexico).</li>
        <li><strong>Social Security:</strong> Includes pension, health, and labor risk provisions legally required for full-time compliant hiring.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. EOR / Management Fees</h2>
      <p>To provide a realistic Total Annual Cost for US companies that do not have local legal entities, we include an estimated $599/month ($7,188/year) management fee, which is the industry standard for premium EOR platforms managing local payroll and compliance.</p>

      <div class="disclaimer">
        <strong>Legal Disclaimer:</strong> The data provided on TalentScaleHQ is for informational and estimation purposes only. It does not constitute legal, tax, or financial advice. Actual hiring costs may vary based on exact location, currency exchange rates, individual negotiations, and changing local labor laws. Always consult with a certified local legal counsel or your Employer of Record before finalizing employment contracts.
      </div>
      
